social_posts.post_text: Art is bigger than that. We can hold two things- we can fight for better pay and keep making work. I love you.

Been reminding myself that things move slow sometimes and that’s ok. My swims have been taking more time in the morning, my walks have been stretching out and this painting I am making for a client is one of my favorite things I’ve been working on and it’s taken longer than I thought. I count myself lucky to get to work with people who understand that my painting practice (illustration is not always afforded this luxury, but that’s it’s nature) takes time. 

You can now sign up for Yellow Brick Road 1&2 and/or Night Class for Winter 2023. I’ll be doing a Q&A in my stories for those of you who want more info or to know what these offerings are like. My hope with these classes is to foster an art practice for you that is generous, intuitive and something unique to you.

Keep making things.

I spent a lot of free time in my childhood arranging and rearranging my room and then in my teens/ya years I started adding painting the walls a new color to the mix- including an unforgettable fudge brown that I still stand by. 

It’s winter break and I am getting back to my roots as I plan larger paintings for the new year! It’s gonna take me awhile to get this space right, but that’s the fun part. In the meantime here is a magic light moment for you ✨
Some things ✨

Easing back into the work schedule by working on this funny little painting or collection of paintings. 

I love how we try to find narrative even when a story isn’t present, it’s something I’ve explored over the years in different ways, and this has been a fun way to think about it.
Back at it- glad Trudi and I took a little time to clear out some space for new work over the break. Real glad to see some sun and a break in the rain ✨

Got to make another poster for @dolphinclubsf i love trying to find ways to give information but also be playful. This was a fast turn around so I kept to more of a drawing style and I had a lot of fun with the limited palette. If you swipe you can see some of the sketches. @zmccune asked me if I could make this and I was happy to- it’s for a Valentine’s Day regatta that Zach is organizing through the club! Fun Fact: Dolphin Club has been around since 1877!

✨image made wider to accommodate this funny platform✨

Hi! My name is @lindsayvictorialee and I’ll be taking over the @closerandcloserco instagram for the week! 

I am based in San Francisco and work with both traditional materials and digital ones depending on the project. I love drawing, problem solving and using texture in m work- and I have a few projects that have allowed me to work really large that have been so fun to work on. If you swipe you can see more work and I’ll list them below!

1. Editorial work for writer Alice Evans
2. Me working on a large painting for a client
3. Some drawing process for a current project
4. Some works in progress
5. Painting for Chick Shack in Cairo, Egypt
6. “A Resting Place” gouache on paper 40x28”
7. Editorial for Alice Evans
8-9. Personal works 
10. Podcast cover art for Here Lies Me

Hi again! It’s @lindsayvictorialee and I thought I would show you a bit of where I work and introduce myself a little more! I’ll be sharing more as the week goes on, looking forward to it!

#workinprogress #studio #illustrator #painting #gouache

Hey everyone! It’s @lindsayvictorialee again, today. I thought I’d show you how I take the sketches I work on with a client and turn it into a final piece. Since I work mostly analogue that might feel a little mysterious ✨ I’ll share a bit more in stories later today! 

#illustration #art #drawing #graphite

Hey! It’s @lindsayvictorialee again and I thought I’d make a little love letter to paint and show you a bit about what happens after a sketch. Pictured are a bunch of mystery paintings for clients. I’ll explain a bit more about what that is in my post today. 

#art #painting #illustration #gouache #watercolor  #acrylicpainting

Hello again! @lindsayvictorialee here to share a personal project of mine- meaning one I semi created for myself, though it does involve clients! In 2015 or 2016 I started doing Mystery Paintings for people who wanted custom work from me. I would send them a questionnaire and they would send me pictures, dreams, stories about themselves- the more descriptive the better. I would then make a painting in response that would feel 100 percent for them- the key here is though- they never see any of it til I finish! Here are two I did in 2022 and one I did a bit before that, and a current giant one I am making for a client! I let that client see some progress pics already, so no surprises ruined here. Me for scale! 

I love making custom work, and I love surprising the people who order them with something that feels deeply personal. 

#painting #art #artist #illustration #paint

Hey guys, its @lindsayvictorialee with another behind the scenes look at a project I loved working on. This was a poster I made for @dolphinclubsf that I hand painted and then edited digitally. And after making the poster I joined my club mates in swimming from the Bay Bridge back to Aquatic Park! It was so fun to make and to share with everyone who helps at the club. Here’s to more fun projects like this!

#painting #posterart #illustration #art #illustrator #gouache #watercolor

Hello there, @lindsayvictorialee sharing one of my favorite projects from last year! I got to make a swim poster for the @dolphinclubsf which I am a member of. They gave me full creative freedom which can feel hard sometimes. But I made constraints for myself, knew I wanted to play around with formatting everything traditionally before bringing it into the digital space for editing. It was a lot of fun and I look forward to more projects like this in the future! 

#illustrator #illustration #paint #gouache #watercolor

Hey there! Its me @lindsayvictorialee just sharing some process from one of my fav client projects from last year! This was an editorial project on systems for Alice Evans and the Omidyar Group. Alice and I had some of the best conversations and really came to an understanding of how she viewed systems and I had a great time figuring out how to translate that into images. I created 7 spots and 3 vignettes for her project and it was challenging in the best way and a lot of fun. You can find more of the finals in a post I’ll share in a bit.

#illustration #editorialillustration #gouache #watercolor #art

Hey there! @lindsayvictorialee again sharing some of the editorial work I did for Alice Evans and Omidyar group this past fall. Alice wanted images to accompany her writing on systems change and it was so incredibly interesting to get to talk to her about systems and systems change and come up with images that would communicate the her concepts in a way that felt true to her. You can see a bit more of the process in the reel I shared today as well!

#illustration #editorialillustration #gouache #watercolor

We’ll friends, it’s been a cool week sharing a bit of myself and my process with you! You can follow along with more process and creative work over on my Instagram @lindsayvictorialee ✨ I teach a lot of different classes on having an art practice if that interests you. You can sign up for my newsletter using the link in my bio to hear more about current projects and things I’m working on.

Thanks for tuning in! I hope to get to work with you in the future.

#illustrator #artist #painting #gouachepainting #watercolor #art

I’ve had the pleasure of working on this painting for the last 6 months for a lovely human who trusted me to make something I thought she’d love. It’s been a true joy to paint and I’m honestly sad to see it go- sometimes certain paintings become much more influential on other works than I realize. I’ll share install details soon. ❤️

Feeling pretty grateful for all the sunrises and that I get to make drawings and paintings for wonderful people. Finally got to hand over the giant painting to its lovely owner yesterday and install it in her home.
Just some things from the weekend 🥳

Been thinking about a swim cycle animation, finally was able to make it happen 🥳 one of my personal goals this year is to get better at animating my work. Something I’ve tried and studied a few times over the years but never stuck with. So hopefully I’ll be making more complex ones moving forward!

#illustration #framebyframe #art #drawing #gouache

Last month @closerandcloserco asked the artists on their roster to make an illustrated label and product mock for a beer, wine or spirits company of their choice for fun. I have played with pretend labels for beers before but had not done a spirit label yet so I chose @spiritworksdistillery and had a lot of fun coming up with something slightly narrative and painterly. 

I love making pretend labels and art- experimenting with what something might look like if it was in my world. This was a lot of fun!
Sometimes I’ll have a thought only for it to sit in my brain for a year before I figure out what it is. After a personal work drought. A new series is born.
A color study for a large painting ✨

Spent the last few months prepping for this mural install for @lululemon in Santa Rosa at @montgomeryvillageca 

Doing a mural takes pretty much every ounce of energy I have- I love doing them and this was by far the most intricate and large one I have ever done. Lots to problem solve, lots of climbing up and down ladders. 

This was also my first time bringing on an assistant and @tropicalspaghetti was joy to have on the drives and job site for the first half of the mural! 

Excited to see it once the new store is opened- which is happening this week. You can see some of the original hand painted color mocks in relation to the mural in this reel- and I think the evolution of those studies and the final are my favorite part.

Day 6- eye from @furrylittlepeach @peachtober had to switch it up and do something that felt fun and easy. Oil pastel mono print using foil 🥳

#peachtober23 #peachtobereye

Really enjoying the process of focusing on drawing and creating these little mono prints. 

I did the first two prompts as a painting and it took me a good amount of time to make a painting I’m just ok with- and it made me realize I was over thinking it. 

Scaling it back and keeping it playful has been a really refreshing approach!

#peachtober23 #peachtobercrater

I haven’t had time to do more inktober drawings but I did do some past ones a few days ago. So here’s #peachtobersprig23 #peachtober23 using oil pastels and foil to make a mono print 🥳 if you’re like me and feeling a bit overwhelmed but want to participate- cut yourself some slack and just show up however you can 😉
